name: ElasticLoadBalancingAccessLoggingPolicy
description: The AccessLoggingPolicy property describes where and how access logs are stored for the AWS::ElasticLoadBalancing::LoadBalancer resource.

properties.name: EmitInterval
properties.description: The interval for publishing access logs in minutes. You can specify an interval of either 5 minutes or 60 minutes.

properties.name: Enabled
properties.description: Whether logging is enabled for the load balancer.

properties.name: S3BucketName
properties.description: The name of an Amazon S3 bucket where access log files are stored.

properties.name: S3BucketPrefix
properties.description: A prefix for the all log object keys, such as my-load-balancer-logs/prod. If you store log files from multiple sources in a single bucket, you can use a prefix to distinguish each log file and its source.
